1309 /*
1310 In ON DUPLICATE KEY clause, it is possible to refer to fields from
1311 the selected tables also, if the query expression is not a VALUES clause,
1312 not a UNION and the query block is not explicitly grouped.
1313
1314 This has implications if ON DUPLICATE KEY values contain subqueries,
1315 due to the way Query_block::apply_local_transforms() is called: it is
1316 usually triggered only on the outer-most query block. Such subqueries
1317 are attached to the last query block of the INSERT statement (relevant if
1318 this is an INSERT statement with a query expression containing UNION).
1319
1320 If the query is INSERT VALUES, processing is quite simple:
1321 - resolve VALUES expressions (above)
1322 - resolve ON DUPLICATE KEY values with same name resolution context.
1323 - call apply_local_transforms() on outer query block.
1324
1325 If the query is INSERT SELECT and the query expression contains UNION,
1326 processing is performed as follows:
1327 - resolve ON DUPLICATE KEY expressions with same name resolution context.
1328 In this case, it is OK to resolve any subqueries before the outer
1329 query block, because references from the expressions into the
1330 tables of the query expression are not allowed.
1331 - resolve the query expression with insert table excluded from name
1332 resolution context. This will implicitly call apply_local_transforms()
1333 on the outer query blocks and all subqueries in ON DUPLICATE KEY
1334 expressions, which are attached to the last query block of the UNION.
1335
1336 If the query is INSERT SELECT and the query expression does not have
1337 a UNION, processing is performed as follows:
1338 - set skip_local_transforms for the outer query block to prevent
1339 apply_local_transforms() from being called.
1340 - resolve the query expression with insert table excluded from name
1341 resolution context.
1342 - if query block is not grouped, combine the name resolution context
1343 for the insert table and the query expression, so that ON DUPLICATE KEY
1344 expressions may refer to all those tables (otherwise restore
1345 name resolution context as insert table only).
1346 - resolve ON DUPLICATE KEY expressions.
1347 - call apply_local_transforms() on outer query block, which also
1348 contains references to any subqueries from ON DUPLICATE KEY expressions.
1349 */
